From: WaveCrux capture pipeline
Subject: [PATCH] Add `aresetn` (active-low) to the FST dump (axil_ram)

Sibling of the closed-source `wavecrux-pro` axi_ram / axi_register
patches — same idea, retargeted at the `axil_ram` (AXI4-Lite) testbench.
The open-core `Axi4LiteDecoder` requires an `aresetn` binding
(active-low synchronous reset). Forencich's testbenches drive `rst`
active-high. We expose the inverted reset in the same testbench-side
dump scope so the FST carries the signal natively — no DUT
modification, no decoder change.

Apply with `patch -p1` from inside `verilog-axi/tb/axil_ram/` after
running `make WAVES=1 SIM=icarus` once to materialize `iverilog_dump.v`:

    patch -p1 < forencich_axil_ram_aresetn_dump.patch

Tested against `alexforencich/verilog-axi` commit
`516bd5dadc3365b7f9e225d2af8fe0b8d804fe53`.

---
 iverilog_dump.v | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/iverilog_dump.v b/iverilog_dump.v
--- a/iverilog_dump.v
+++ b/iverilog_dump.v
@@ -1,5 +1,7 @@
 module iverilog_dump();
+wire aresetn = !axil_ram.rst;
 initial begin
     $dumpfile("axil_ram.fst");
     $dumpvars(0, axil_ram);
+    $dumpvars(0, iverilog_dump.aresetn);
 end
 endmodule
